10_32	2.3333333333333335	It's clear that from decade to decade the nature of El Nino does change.
10_33	2.1	From 1885 to 1915, for example, El Ninos were powerful, but from 1915 to 1950 they were minuscule.
10_34	0.0	After 1960 they picked up again, and since the late 1970s they've been very big.
10_35	1.5714285714285714	The work of researchers, combined with El Nino's power this year, has made clear that it is far more than a matter of the occasional bad fish catch.
10_36	1.6153846153846154	El Nino represents the fickleness of a powerful ocean that can focus its energy on the world's weather with stunning swiftness.
10_37	0.0	Cane and Zebiak have recently been studying the quirkiness of the Pacific on the scale of hundreds of thousands of years.
